  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Current situation\r\n=============\r\nCurrently Swarm is included in the ethereum package at `https://launchpad.net/~ethereum/+archive/ubuntu/ethereum/+packages` and in the \"geth and tools\" package at `https://geth.ethereum.org/downloads/`\r\n\r\nThis means that\r\n\r\n- Swarm package uses Geth version number (currently 1.8.11) instead of swarm's own version 0.3.0\r\n- A new swarm binary is released whenever a new geth version is tagged (and only then)\r\n\r\nWhat we'd like\r\n============\r\n\r\n- The swarm package should track swarm's version\r\n- It should be possible to trigger a new release of swarm without a new geth release and vice versa.\r\n\r\n",
